Viva explanation (2 marks)

If the examiner asks "What is Spark Streaming?", you can answer:

Spark Streaming is used to process real-time incoming data. In this practical, Spark continuously monitors the stream_data folder. Whenever a new text file is added, it reads the file, splits the text into words, counts the occurrences of each word, and displays the updated result on the console.

